# Day 18 – AWS Backup & Disaster Recovery

## Goal
Learn how to protect and restore AWS resources using AWS Backup.

## Steps
- Created backup plan for EC2 and RDS.
- Scheduled daily backups.
- Ran on-demand backup and verified snapshot.
- Simulated disaster by deleting resource.
- Restored resource from backup vault.
- Verified restored resource worked correctly.

## Lessons Learned
- AWS Backup automates snapshots and recovery.
- RPO = how much data you can afford to lose.
- RTO = how fast you need to recover.
- Disaster recovery planning is essential for customer trust.
